````markdown
# Socialface

**Socialface** is a powerful, AI-enhanced full-stack social media platform inspired by Facebook. It offers real-time communication, intelligent chatbots, audio/video calling, media sharing, and secure authentication—built with modern web technologies.

🚀 [Live Demo](https://socialface-eight.vercel.app/)  
📦 [GitHub Repository](https://github.com/salmansadiq1015/Socialface)

---

## 📌 Features

- ✅ **Authentication & Authorization**  
  - JWT + NextAuth integration  
  - Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

- 💬 **Real-Time Chat & Typing Indicators**  
  - Private and group messaging with WebSockets  
  - Real-time typing and seen statuses

- 📞 **Audio/Video Calling**  
  - ZegoCloud-powered one-on-one and group calls  
  - Audio-only & video modes

- 🤖 **AI Chatbot & Document Q&A**  
  - Chat with AI using OpenAI  
  - Upload PDFs and get answers using LLM embeddings

- 📸 **Media & Stories**  
  - Upload and preview images, videos, and audio files  
  - Auto-delete stories after 20 hours

- 📈 **Analytics Dashboard**  
  - Real-time insights on user engagement  
  - Admin panel for data management

- 💰 **Payments Integration**  
  - Stripe and PayPal for donations & in-app purchases

- ⚡ **Performance & Deployment**  
  - Redis for caching  
  - Deployed on Vercel + AWS + GCP

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

**Frontend:**
- Next.js
- React.js
- Tailwind CSS
- Redux Toolkit
- Framer Motion

**Backend:**
- Node.js
- Express.js
- MongoDB
- Redis
- WebSockets (Socket.io)

**Third-Party APIs:**
- OpenAI (Chatbot, PDF QA)
- ZegoCloud (Audio/Video Calling)
- Twilio (Messaging Support)
- Stripe / PayPal (Payments)
- Google APIs (Auth, Maps, etc.)

**Auth & Security:**
- JWT
- NextAuth.js
- Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

---

## 🔧 Installation

1. **Clone the repo**
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/salmansadiq1015/Socialface.git
   cd Socialface
````

2. **Install dependencies**

   ```bash
   npm install
   # or
   yarn install
   ```

3. **Set up environment variables**

   Create `.env.local` file and add your credentials:

   ```env
   MONGODB_URI=
   JWT_SECRET=
   NEXTAUTH_SECRET=
   NEXTAUTH_URL=
   STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
   STRIPE_PUBLIC_KEY=
   OPENAI_API_KEY=
   ZEGO_APP_ID=
   ZEGO_SERVER_SECRET=
   REDIS_URL=
   ```

4. **Run the development server**

   ```bash
   npm run dev
   ```

